+{"parentUuid":"8cec3406-8a8a-4b59-9ba3-6f6138d45fa0","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/workspace","sessionId":"c72847a7-f90d-4e5c-8550-f6d55cbba82a","version":"2.1.63","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"smooth-greeting-origami","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01QDMH78GXCj2WxJWjeZF3aB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. I need to create `src/index.ts` with two functions:\n\n1. `simulate` - straightforward topological simulation\n2. `findSwappedWires` - the tricky part, finding 4 pairs of swapped output wires in a ripple-carry adder\n\nLet me think about the `findSwappedWires` algorithm carefully.\n\nA ripple-carry adder for N bits has this structure:\n\n**Bit 0 (half adder):**\n- x00 XOR y00 -> z00 (sum)\n- x00 AND y00 -> c00 (carry)\n\n\n**Bit i (full adder, for i = 1..N-1):**\n- x_i XOR y_i -> t_i (partial sum)\n- t_i XOR c_{i-1} -> z_i (final sum)\n- x_i AND y_i -> a_i (generate carry)\n- t_i AND c_{i-1} -> b_i (propagate carry)\n- a_i OR b_i -> c_i (carry out)\n**Final bit:**\n- c_{N-1} -> z_N (final carry)\n\nSo for each bit position, I know the expected structure and can use this to identify which wires are swapped by checking which outputs don't match their expected values. For bit 0: Find the XOR gate with inputs x00, y00 - its output should be z00. Find the AND gate with inputs x00, y00 - its output is the carry.\n\nFor each subsequent bit i: \n   - Find the XOR gate with inputs x_i, y_i - this gives the partial sum wire (call it t_i)\n   - Find the XOR gate with inputs t_i, carry_{i-1} - its output should be z_i\n   - Find the AND gate with inputs x_i, y_i - this gives generate carry\n   - Find the AND gate with inputs t_i, carry_{i-1} - this gives propagate carry\n   - Find the OR gate with one of generate and propagate as inputs - this gives carry_i\n\nIf any wire is in the wrong place, we can detect it.\n\nThe key is to structurally analyze each bit position an